description:
&lt;p&gt;East Suffolk and North Essex NHS Foundation Trust has a variety of exciting nursing opportunities both full and part time in medicine based at Colchester Hospital on a fixed term and permanent basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have opportunities in:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Assessment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respiratory Medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stroke Medicine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cardiology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Endocrine&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will require flexibility as you may be required to work within all areas of the Medicine division depending on the needs of the service. This is a perfect opportunity to broaden your knowledge and gain experience in all specialties of medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be working with friendly, motivated, supportive teams to provide excellent patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for individuals who are keen to develop and deliver excellent clinical care. You must be motivated to drive forward and improve the services for the population of Colchester and surrounding area. In turn, we are keen to give you the opportunity to develop your skills whilst supporting you in your career development. We look forward to meeting you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samantha Thorne, Senior Recruitment Partner : Samantha.Thorne@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
